      1 
      تَرِحَ, aor. 

      تَرَحَ, inf. n. تَرَحٌ, He grieved; he
was, or became, sorrowful, unhappy, or anxious;
(Msb, K;) syn. حَزِنَ; (Msb;) [contr. of فَرِحَ;
(see تَرَحٌ, below;)] as also ↓ تترّح. (K.) ― 
       -b2- 
[Also He perished, or died: became cut off;
was put an end to; or came to an end: so accord.
to explanations of تَرَحٌ given below on the authority of IAth.]


      هُوَ أَتْقَى مِنْ فُلَانٍ [He is more fearing, or
cautious, &c., than such a one; more reverentially, or piously, fearful of God; or more pious;
&c.;] he has more تَقْوَى than such a one. (TA.)


      تَلُوٌّ A man incessantly following: (IAar, M,
K:) not mentioned by Yaakoob among the instances of this measure which he has limited;
as حَسُوٌّ and فَسُوٌّ. (M.)


      تَائِجٌ Having a تَاج [i. e. crown, or (assumed tropical:)  turban];
an epithet applied to an إِمَام: (K:) it is a possessive epithet, like دَارِعٌ, for we have not heard
any verb answering to it. (TA.)


      تَوٍ (S M, Mgh, K) and ↓ تَاوٍ (Mgh) Perishing;
coming to an end; (S, Mgh, K;) passing away
(M, Mgh) unhoped for: (M:) applied to property. (S, M, Mgh.)
